<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06180106 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06180106 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  US; COURT; RULING; SALE; LONDON; AVIATION; TRAVEL; TRANSPORTATION; COMPANY;FACILITY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A divided federal appeals court today upheld the sale of four London routes byTrans World Airlines to American Airlines, clearing the way for American toget into London's Heathrow Airport next week.;    Missouri politicians andTWA's unions fear the deal will kill TWA, however.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  COURT CLEARS SALE OF TWA LONDON ROUTES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     In a 2-1 opinion, the 8th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals allowed twoDepartment of Transportation orders to stand, clearing the way for thetransfers of three of the routes to take effect Monday.;    American Airlineshas been advertising and selling tickets for those routes -- from New York,Los Angeles and Boston -- since the sale was approved by TransportationSecretary Samuel Skinner on April 24.;    A fourth route -- Chicago-London --was allowed Jan. 30 and American has been operating it since then.;    Thecity of St. Louis and three TWA unions had challenged Skinner's decisions,saying it was not in the best interests of the general public or TWA.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  St. Louis  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910628  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  12D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  155  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday June 28, 199100180106,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>